                            <comment id="14071422" author="julienlehuen" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2014 06:40:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is &lt;b&gt;critical&lt;/b&gt; for Impala users! We want to be able to perform our Metastore operations via Hive&apos;s Thrift server, but this would create unhealthy tables for which we can not run ANALYZE. Such table&apos;s statistics cannot computed by Impala (statistics are absolutely necessary for Impala to run joins in an optimal manner), and this means that we need to create table via Impala over JDBC. This is less than ideal, and this issue is the only blocker from letting us create via Hive over Thrift.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Related IMPALA tickets: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.cloudera.org/browse/IMPALA-867&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;IMPALA-867&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.cloudera.org/browse/IMPALA-1104&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;IMPALA-1104&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
